Title: Ralph Breaks the Internet: Wreck-It Ralph 2 Official Trailer
Comment: This seriously looks brilliant. I love the trailer, although I have to point out that this is yet another Disney movie that somehow forgets to include Megara in the Princess line up - well, she's married to a demigod instead of a Prince - but come on! Hercules is one of the best Disney films ever made; it has the best villain, incredible songs from Alan Menkin and Megara, the first, truly independent female role. She comes from nothing, sells her soul to the devil to save her boyfriend's (Achilles) life, who then cheats on her and still she manages to pull her life together. Surely that should be a good enough reason to include more of her? I know, I know, Hercules wasn't as popular as all the other films the Princesses shown in Ralph 2 were and there would be a real uproar if Elsa was without Anna (or would there be?), but these Princesses get all the screen time in all the movies and wouldn't it be great to bring some of the others in from time-to-time? Like Kida from Atlantis who is definitely a Princess (another amazing film) or Esmeralda from Hunchback who is definitely not a Princess but comes from a film which has the most breathtaking score. And wouldn't it be great to introduce these characters to a new generation who will then go back and watch the films and realise how amazing they are? Frozen was and still is the most successful and popular Disney film of all time, but that doesn't make it the best Disney film of all time. You put it alongside Beauty and the Beast, Aladdin or Hercules - it still stands up as one of the greats, but not the greatest. Of course you need to keep bringing Elsa and Anna into the mix as they are still relevant, but you're Disney. If you can make an arcade game from almost 40 years ago relevant again, surely you can do the same for some of your "forgotten" Princesses? I know I'm rambling and probably sounding like a proper geek, but I'm proud of being a geek and a huge Disney fanboy. I may be in my 30s now, but Disney appeals to all ages and let's us all know that it's ok to appease our inner child. There are 56 animated Disney movies with most having either a Princess or a strong female lead. As we are all born at different times, we all have our favourites and it would be great if they could all seen again, from time to time.

This movie just seems to be attempting to market Disney and to fit as many references to pop culture as it can into the movie. The reasons I feel this movie will be bad are

1.  From this trailer, this movie will most likely have a shallow plot wit the basis of saving the internet. 

2.  It will most likely not have any character development considering we got all the development that was possible between Ralp and Candy girl

3. The amount of pop culture references of today's society basically just sjows this movie is going to pander to Kids and is going to have jokes that just fall flat.

The 1st movie was so good because we got to see such good development between all the characters in the movie. The movie also ended on a satisfying note with Ralph and candy girl becoming happy with their lives. There was really no point in making a second movie and its obvious that this movie was made just to cash out on the popularity of the 1st one.

Title: Ralph Breaks the Internet: Wreck-It Ralph 2 Official Trailer
Comment:
People are saying that this film is just seems it's gonna 'end up like the emoji movie'. This is just my opinion on the matter. Let's look at the facts:

This is a Disney Animation film, which hopefully means it won't need too much advertising, since Disney don't need it. Sure it has things like twitter, amazon and google shown on it. But that's because it's the internet. Those are 3 of the biggest names on it, of course they are gonna be featured. It wouldn't be the internet without it. Also the search bar guy could have easily been Google.
The other companies were only shown for a second maybe two each. The biggest advertisement was for Disney and other companies it owns.
The emoji movie was also a film based off emoji's, a really dumb concept when you think about. I haven't watched it because I've never wanted to but I know enough about it that it doesn't make sense. (Is their a thing as a 'just dance' app?)

This is a sequel to a successful film that will expand the world for characters people already know and like. Plus it's the same director and one of the same writers as the first one, so they should know what they are doing.

Other opinions:

Sure they advertised other companies Disney owns. But this is the sequel to a film which had several game characters from different franchises on the same screen. Of course they are gonna do the same thing again with stuff Disney owns. It's it character for what they did in the first one.
Honestly, I find it great that they did. Seeing a X-Wing, Iron Man, EVE and Kermit on the same screen was something I never saw coming.

I knew from a news thing awhile back that they were gonna do the princess thing so I'm not shocked they put it in the trailer. But honestly, I find how they did it hilarious. And I like the fact that they got the princesses respective actresses to reprise their roles (except ones who have passed away). I'm pretty sure it's gonna be for that one scene though.

When I first saw the title for this film, I thought it was gonna be a bit weird. But now, I think this is gonna be a really good film and I'm really excited about watching it.

Insainely if this plot is excuted Correctly It could work really well.... 

Think of it this way this movie is based off a world of capitalism  which it was built. If the story arch progresses in such a way.... which no doubt it probably will that will see the end of a highly commercialised world of the movies own creation. The movie in itself would likely end up being a good commentary for internet commercialisation and the never ending relyance on the internet. When you concider relph saying he wants to destroy "break" the internet and add a good character dynamic, along with noticable brands and a storyline as to why it would be nessersary. It would highlight what happens if such an internet would fail in a modern day environment.

Do this incorrectly you face the risk of destroying noticeable characters. This medium is always a risky move. Do it incorrectly it could be an emjoii movie or worse... you would have to be either a brave writer or a foolish writer to attempt it

Also disney poking fun at themselves was amusing.

Title: Ralph Breaks the Internet: Wreck-It Ralph 2 Official Trailer
Comment:
I REALLY wanna like this movie, but I hate this trailer more every time I watch it. 

0:00 No reason given for WHY they're going to the internet, just... what I assume was supposed to be a joke? 

0:53 Dated joke where we aren't even told what they're looking for. 

1:18 This part was kinda funny, but we still have no idea what ANY of it has to do with the story. 

2:08 Really? You named your whole movie that just for one lamp shading joke? Lamp shading only works if you somehow subvert the trope you're lamp shading! Also, I hate these millennial consultant characters: older people don't get them, younger people feel unjustifiably insulted by them, and the only people in on the joke are the people that made the movie! They aren't fun, they aren't likable, and every minute they're on screen is another minute you want them to go away.

Just watch the trailer for the original movie again if you wanna see how product placement and nostalgic pandering can be funny AND seamlessly integrated into the story in only two minutes.

Wow.

to get to the point where you

is automatically color-corrected,

into this soothing sweet syrup

  
with its distinctive

Honey!

to improve every aspect

the Krelman.

that hangs after you pour it.

Oan anyone work on the Krelman?

  
Of course. Most bee jobs are
small ones. But bees know

  
that every small job,
if it's done well, means a lot.

  
But choose carefully

  
because you'll stay in the job
you pick for the rest of your life.

  
The same job the rest of your life?

doing the same job every day?

move it around, and you stir it around.

the more I think about it,

  
maybe the honey field

Janet, your son's not sure

Title: Ralph Breaks the Internet: Wreck-It Ralph 2 Official Trailer
Comment: I was such a big fan of the first movie, amazing story and characters. But this feels like they're putting product placement and "social justice" before story. I have nothing against social justice but I hate when it's blatantly rubbed in my face just to appeal to people before they make a hash tag that needlessly destroys a franchise. Seriously, you never see Mulan stop in the middle of the story to make a speech about being a strong woman while slipping in a line about Disney's new movies. I look at this trailer and I don't see a team of passionate writers, I see fifty people in business suits deciding where to slip in the next star wars reference and then deciding not to subtlety slip it in but have Ralph scream "I Love Star Wars Because It Has Strong Female Characters." I know some people think it's just a kids movie but I'm wanted to rant a bit after seeing that. Hope other people understand where I'm coming from.

The first Wreck-It-Ralph had a lot of real world references, but they were worked into the story.
This feels more like mass advertising at Emoji movie levels.

Plus, why is it that any movie that depicts the internet as a living world feels like it was written by a pre-2000s old person?
I'm not against the idea of the internet being a living world i movies, it just always feels dated no matter how current the references are, and not quite right. It's always as though all the internet ever is is a series of billboards.

Title: Ralph Breaks the Internet: Wreck-It Ralph 2 Official Trailer
Comment:
So Disney is just going to go through and destroy all it's proprieties again?
1:37 that's not how those (most of) Princesses would react they're not fighters. 
Especially the classic ones, Snow white, Cinderella, Aurora, it's very out of character for them.
But instead of having the more feisty/worrier princesses stand at the ready 
and the more gentile and meek ones hide they just made them all jump up.

All of these charterers are established and the original ones were very sincere and now they make them all porridge.
Now they've made them milk toast just blandly strong, knowing, and independent
Which takes away the uniqueness of the ones who were always like that.

Let's not forget that the men who saved them (if you really want to take it that literally) 
are all very good and great men.
For goodness sake Aurora's "Big strong man" slayed a dragon and woke her from eternal sleep. 
You'd have to be a little thick to take fairy tails literally but they will.
But even if you do that, how can you possibly think that "a big strong man" is a bad thing?
As if having a good, strong, brave man around would be a bad or demeaning thing.
Or that being so good, kind, hard working, pure, and loving that you inspire someone to take up arms and defend you when you're too weak to do anything ( because of the multiple assassination attempts) is wrong.

O.K. I'm starting to cool down and I know I shouldn't condemn a move based on a 2 minuet  trailer.
I know that is kind of what I'm doing. 
For those of you how made it through the dark times that were the Cinderella straight to DVD sequels you will understand why I'm so defensive. 
It hurts when you see the characters you love and grew up with changed to fit with the agenda of the month attitude.
I've seen this happen to those who love star wars  and saw the prequels and were hurt and now the new ones, oi va.
I actually don't know about Star Wars that's just what I've been seeing. Which Disney also owns now... hmm.

Wow I didn't think my comment would get this long. 
I guess this isn't really about Wreck-It Ralph more on the whole princess zeitgeist as is stands.
I hope this was just an overreaction by me and the move is good but I'm weary of sequels.

Well thanks for reading this maybe if you feel the way I do you enjoyed this supper long comment. <3
-Lily 

P.S. the classic princesses look really bad with the new CGI.

Comment: My name is Bella Thorne, and this is the story of the time I found out I had dyslexia. I remember when I started first grade. Title: Ralph Breaks the Internet: Wreck-It Ralph 2 Official Trailer
Comment:
Some people may argue against the comment Rapunzel makes but she is correct. It is a bit of a misconception for the most part in regards to the Disney Princess movies. 

When you analyze the films more, at most I would say Aurora, Jasmine, and kind of Snow White had their problems solved from a male. To be fair to Snow White, she is about 14, and her problems were solved with the help of multiple male adults, such as the hunter, the dwarves, then finally the prince.  Oh, and Ariel too I suppose since Prince Eric defeats Ursula in the end although her problems weren't "solved" until her father granted her legs.

Cinderella's problems were solved due to a fairy Godmother and deciding to rebel, and then coincidentally falling in love.  Tiana and Rapunzel were a strange set of partnered circumstances that were originally mutual agreements between both parties that are helping each other and then a conflict with Dr. Facilier and Mother Gothel. Pocahontas actually gained problems due to John and the other colonists searching for gold. And we certainly can't include Mulan, Merrida, Anna, Elsa, or Alice in not solving their problems. Moana had some prophecy stuff to get Maui and mostly saves the day herself.

It's kind of strange that Disney has this reputation in regards to their Princess films as they really aren't like that at all for the most part. Perhaps due to marketing, toys, etc and particularly from past Disney which was founded in the 20s but not the actual movies. Sorry my comment was so long and I was still trying to be thorough while keeping it short! ^-^

Comment: You know, I don't even have to predict that its going to be a gigantic billion dollar box office hit. I don't don't even have to predict that will have a high rating on rotten tomatoes. Never have I laughed so hard at a movie that would not only be better than the original, but also more exciting than the original too. I guess I could see it in theaters and have a fun time seeing it. But still, funny, laughable, suprising, great visuals, and tuns of humor, Ralph breaks the internet is going to be a feel good to watch movie that I will hail as a masterpiece. I still can't believe they featured the Princesses in one scene.

But Pocahontas was the first, and it's a shame Mulan isn't in there, because she saved all of China. Like I said, the joke lands, but they had plenty of strong female characters in that room who did not fit that mold.

Title: Ralph Breaks the Internet: Wreck-It Ralph 2 Official Trailer
Comment:
In general, this looks like an interesting movie. Despite an abundance of product placement and self-promotion, there does seem to be some creativity and effort put into how the internet is depicted (but is it just me, or has The Emoji Movie tainted this concept a little?). I just hope it has at least one reference to Tron, and perhaps a cameo from Jack Sparrow.  

What bothers me though is some of the self-parodying that the princesses do. Sure, they do reference the most stereotypical themes associated with themselves, and feel cleverly used as Jonas Brothers-esque performers, but other than that it feels a bit disrespectful. Not as much to the characters as to the people who in the earlier days of Disney helped create them. Snow White, for instance, is a character that has admittedly aged, but from a seniority point of view, she should feel a bit more dignified. She was the very first Disney princess after all, in the first feature-length animated movie ever. And as much as I enjoy that Disney are willing to make fun of themselves, didn't they already do that with Enchanted? Also, do they really need to hammer the point of feminism in when they already have characters like Elsa, Mulan and Belle present? 

I also have a fear that Wreck-it Ralph 2, like a lot of movies right now, will lean too heavily on nostalgia in order to sell itself to an audience. Admittedly it did the same with videogame characters in the first one, but the references it made fit the mold of the story and didn't distract from our main characters. Because Ralph and Vanellope seems to be out of their element for most of the movie, the risk of the movie feeling like a huge sidetrack might be higher.

Though I'm not gonna jump the gun yet and say that this will be stupid, cause I do like some of the stuff I've seen here. The Disney-princesses look pretty good in this format, and some of their other characteristics are cleverly used, like how Pocahontas hair appears to have a constant breeze in it, or that Cinderella uses her glass slipper like a broken bottle.

Mickey Mouse, Dumbo, Kermit the Frog, Iron Man, Eve, Arlo, R2D2, X-Wing Star Fighter, Tie Fighter, Pixar Lamp on Pixar Ball (in Andy's room I would say), Jolly Roger in front of Big Ben, Millenium Falcon in front of Death Star, the Sorcerer's Hat, Captain America's shield, Chesire Cat, Lady and Tramp, Simba and Pumon, Buzz Lightyear, Woody, Jessie, the Jungle Book movie poster, the Door and energy can from Monster's Inc., and the Up house.

No, I do not regret it.

A great amount of detail, Disney. I'm impressed and can't wait for this movie!
